<HEADLINE> Security Tightened for U.S. Embassy in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The United States has tightened
security for its embassy in Nicosia following the air raids on
Afghanistan and Sudan, the Cyprus News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The U.S. embassy is taking appropriate security measures in
light of recent events," the agency quoted an embassy spokesman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
There have been enhancements and security precautions taken,
the spokesman said, without going into details.
</P>
<P>
"We are satisfied with the excellent co-operation we have
received from local authorities," he added.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. launched air raids Thursday night on what it called
terrorist facilities in Afghanistan and Sudan in retaliation for
the August 7 twin bombings against its embassies in Kenya and
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Security has been tightened for all U.S. diplomatic missions
abroad for fear of retaliatory attacks by Islamic militants.
</P>
</TEXT>
