<HEADLINE> Germany Rules Out State Funds for Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl
Friday ruled out new state credits in the near future to
Russia in response to the latest financial crisis there.
</P>
<P>
The question of new credits "did not pose itself," he said,
while calling on Russia to move forward with its restructuring.
</P>
<P>
"The Russian side must continue its reform efforts," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Kohl had a telephone conversation with his French counterpart
Jacques Chirac about Russian financial problems earlier Friday and
plans to call Russian President Boris Yeltsin Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
