<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Drops 7 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Friday closed at 2,922.61,
showing a decrease of 66.99 points from the previous close of
2,989.60.
</P>
<P>
The national index closed at 1,308.82, with a fall of 27.55
points from the last close of 1,336.37.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 ended lower at 304.75 and the U.S. dollar index at
119.19 from the previous close of 309.70 and 120.61 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Pivotals plummeted on the stock market in Bombay on heavy
selling pressure by foreign institutional investors, who squared
up their positions on the last day of the current settlement, and
inadequate support by the local funds and institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
