<HEADLINE> Turkey Supports U.S. Air Strikes on Afghanistan, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Ministry said
Friday Turkey strongly supports the United States' air strikes
against the "terrorist bases" in Afghanistan and Sudan.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the ministry said that Turkey
condemns all kinds of terrorism whatever its sources or purposes,
and is one of the main supporters of the international cooperation
in the struggle against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey strongly supports the bilateral and international
cooperation agreements against terrorism," it said.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that Turkey shares the determination of the
U.S. that no country should allow terrorists to use its land to
conduct terror activities and harm the civilians.
</P>
<P>
Calling terrorism "the largest danger threatening humanity,"
the statement said that it can be prevented only with an effective
and serious international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the U.S. Embassy in Turkey has informed the Turkish
Foreign Ministry of the missile strikes against suspected
"terrorist sites" in Afghanistan and Sudan Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
The embassy defended the U.S. air strikes against Afghanistan
and Sudan, saying they were acts of "self-defense."  
</P>
</TEXT>
