<HEADLINE> China's Biggest Oil Field Continues Operation Despite Well Closures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAQING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Raging floods in northeast China
have swamped 1,443 oil wells at Daqing Oil Field, the largest in
China.
</P>
<P>
Of the total number, 282 wells have been closed, cutting output
by 13,455 tons in the past nine days ending Thursday, an oilfield
official said today.
</P>
<P>
Other oil wells in the field are in normal production,
however. The oil field today shipped 154,626 tons of oil to
Qinhuangdao Port through pipes, the highest in recent days, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In Harbin, capital of China's northernmost province of
Heilongjiang, motor vehicles bound for Daqing had to go over an
old highway bridge, as traffic on the approach to the new bridge
was suspended on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
