<HEADLINE> French PM Backs U.S. Strikes on Sudan, Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin Friday expressed support for the missile attacks by the
United States against Sudan and Afghanistan Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We should make a determined and firm response against
terrorism wherever it attacks," said Jospin during a meeting with
British Prime Minister Tony Blair in Cintegabelle, southwest
France.
</P>
<P>
He said that "great nations whose flesh has been hurt cannot
remain insensitive."
</P>
<P>
"We repeat our firm condemnation of terrorism in whatever form
it takes, under whatever circumstances it comes up, and the need
to fight it, notably through international cooperation among
nations," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that terrorism should be fought according to
international law because that would be the most effective way to
deal with it.
</P>
<P>
A French Foreign Ministry communique said earlier that France
thinks the terrorist attacks in Nairobi and Dar es Salaam should
not go unanswered. 
</P>
