<HEADLINE> Two New Book Stores open in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Two book stores located on the
Hong Kong Island were opened by the Commercial Press (Hong Kong)
Ltd. here Friday afternoon to meet the growing needs of readers.
</P>
<P>
These are two different moods of book stores, one called
"Community Bookstore" covering a floor space of about 300 square
meters which is the largest of its kind in the district, and the
other named "Personal Bookstore" with a floor space of more than
100 square meters mainly serving for those who are working in the
tall commercial office buildings.
</P>
<P>
Various kinds of books covering a wide range of subjects such
as economy, culture, medicine, education, language learning,
computers, enterprise management are on sale in the "Community
Bookstore".
</P>
<P>
M. H. Chan, general manager of the Commercial press (Hong Kong)
 Ltd., said at the opening ceremony that "Community Bookstore" has
 characteristics of comprehensiveness and bilinguals while the
"Personal Bookstore" demonstrates a concept of "oasis of the city"
 where the people working in the tall commercial office buildings
can take a rest while reading.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan, president of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, described the newly opening of the
two book stores as "significant," adding that the Hong Kong
residents will have more places to absorb knowledge.
</P>
<P>
With a history of 101 years, the Commercial press (Hong Kong)
Ltd. first set up its book store in 1914. 
</P>
</TEXT>
