<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Emphasizes Importance of Science, Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) --- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
today urged officials at all levels to earnestly implement the
national strategy of revitalizing China through science and
education.
</P>
<P>
"Party and government officials at all levels must be role
models in paying keen attention to science and education," Li
said, while talking with 20 distinguished scientists and 34
outstanding teachers at the Great Hall of the People here.
</P>
<P>
Officials must implement the strategy of revitalizing the
nation through science and education with real action rather than
just paying lip service, said Li, who is also a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
He said that investment in science and education must be
increased and efforts be made to improve the living and working
conditions of scientists and teachers.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also be made to industrialize scientific
research achievements to serve economic development and social
advances, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, the scientists and teachers were given the
honor of being received by President Jiang Zemin; Li Peng,
chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress; Premier Zhu Rongji; and Li Ruihuan, Chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference.
</P>
<P>
Others who received the scientists and teachers
include Hu Jintao and Wei Jianxing, both member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The scientists included Wang Xuan, an academician of both the
Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the Chinese Academy of
Engineering (CAE) and a professor at Beijing University; Ke
Jianyi, a research fellow of the CAS; and Wang Chengwei, a CAE
academician. The teachers included Qiu Jilong, headmaster of
Beijing No. 4 High School, and Li Jilin, a teacher from east
China's Jiangsu Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
