<HEADLINE> Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Tumbles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Istanbul Stock Exchange
National-100 Index dropped 4.60 percent, or 160.73 points, to
close at 3,372.29 points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The fall was believed to be related to the U.S. air strikes
against Afghanistan and Sudan on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The trading was active with the turnover reaching over 97
trillion Turkish Liras (about 352 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The financial index dipped 206.51 points, or 4.78 percent, to
close at 4,161.61 points, the industrial index lost 136.23 points,
or 4.60 percent, to close at 2,858.01 points, and the service
index fell 94.17 points, or 2.19 percent, to close at 4,197.67
points. 
</P>
