<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Endorses 4,460 Investment Projects in 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investmeht
Authority said Friday that it has licensed 4,460 investment
projects since the issuance of the Investment Code in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The aggregate investment capital has exceeded 36.9 billion
Birr or 5.2 billion U.S. Dollars, said the authority.
</P>
<P>
It said local and foreign investors were issued with licenses
in various sectors including agriculture, construction, and
mining over the past six years.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 projects to the tune of eight billion Birr(2.1
billion U.S.,7llars) are run by foreign entrepreneurs, said the
authority.
</P>
<P>
It added that the total of nearly 1,000 projects worth eight
billion Birr had entered the production phase by March 1998.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia issued tzhe Investment Code in 1992, which was revised
twice in 1996 and 1997 respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to the revised code, both local and foreign
investors are now allowed to engage in telecommunications,
hydro-electric power genernation and defense industries, with the
last two to be undertaken in cooperation with the government.
