<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Taxi Divers Collect Money for Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The 2,000-odd taxi drivers in
Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian Province, volunteered to
donate their total incomes from today's fares to flood areas,
responding to a call to make flood donations.
</P>
<P>
Zhuang Minxi, Huang Duanfang, Wang Xuefeng and seven other taxi
drivers wrote a letter to a local newspaper on Aug. 16, in which
they called on their colleagues to collect money for flooded areas
and join their campaign "to drive for flooded areas for a day,"
which was held today.
</P>
<P>
The Straits Capital Newspaper published the letter, as well as
two hot-line telephone numbers. The campaign won favorable support
from both local taxi companies and drivers.
</P>
<P>
The money collected today will be donated to Jianli County,
Hubei Province, one of the most serious flood-hit areas in China.
</P>
