<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Commodity Website Booms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- China's first official entry
into electronic commerce has been highly successful and the nation
enjoys a promising future related activities.
</P>
<P>
The government website for commodities has recorded over 10
million hits since its opening in July.
</P>
<P>
The Internet website -- http://www.chinamarket.com.cn --
established by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC), was officiated on July 8 and has since
blossomed into a major link providing information on commodities
carrying the label "Made in China".
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC's China International Electronic Commerce Center (CIECC)
administrator the website, which has attracted millions of hits
from people in more than 80 countries and regions, including a
record 470,000 hits in a single day.
</P>
<P>
Experts point to the fact that the highly successful beginning
reflects the promising future for using advanced information
technology to expand foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Some 82.7 percent of the total hits to the website originated
from abroad, with domestic hits accounting 17.3 percent of the
total.
</P>
<P>
The vast majority of inquiries centered on textile, electronic
and hardware commodities.
</P>
<P>
Virtually, unknown companies, including a dyestuff company, an
electromagnetic products manufacturer and a company producing
clothing for babies received the most attention.
</P>
<P>
Small to medium-sized enterprises accounted for a majority of
the 2,000 ventures linked to the website.
</P>
<P>
A recent CIECC survey of 100 businesses linked to the website
found that 72 percent of the ventures received clear feedbacks.
</P>
<P>
One Hangzhou trade company listed 14 textile commodities in
July and has since received 10-odd favorable inquiries from Japan,
the Republic of Korea (ROK), Australia, the United States and
Canada. The company manager expressed great satisfication with the
response and noted that additional products will offered via the
web market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
