<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, August 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- One of the U.S. missiles aimed at suspected
terrorist targets in Afghanistan landed in Pakistan, killing at
least five people, a Foreign Ministry spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said it seems there had been some technical
error. (Pakistan-US Missile)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KHARTOUM -- Sudanese President General Omar Bashir said Friday
that the Sudan will not submit to the U.S. tyrannical force,
calling upon the Sudanese people to reject the U.S. hegemony.
</P>
<P>
Bashir made the remark at a news conference held here following
an emergency session of the Sudanese National Security and Defense
Council to discuss the Thursday bombing of a Sudanese factory by
U.S. warplanes. (Sudan-US Attack)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- One of the militant groups hit by U.S. missiles
inside Afghanistan has vowed to retaliate against the
U.S. attacks on its base in Khost province of Afghanistan, which
it said is in fact a training camp for the Kashmiri Mujahideen.
</P>
<P>
Chief of Harkat ul Mujahideen, Fazal-ur-Rahman Khalil, whose
organization has close links with Saudi dissident Osama bin Laden,
announced Friday that his organization would respond to the
U.S. "naked aggression" against Afghanistan.
(Pakistan-U.S. Attack-Afghan Group)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian Foreign Ministry on Friday expressed
"serious worries" over U.S. air strikes on Sudan and Afghanistan,
while the State Duma, or lower house of parliament, condemned the
move as an aggression.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin, who was observing a naval exercise of
the Northern Fleet in the Barents Sea at the time, also expressed
indignation over the U.S. military action, said presidential
spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky. (Russia-US-Air Strikes)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- South African President Nelson Mandela is set
to hold peace talks Saturday, which will bring together presidents
of the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), Uganda and Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is the culmination of two weeks' diplomacy of
South Africa to secure a peaceful solution to the conflict in the
DRC, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported Friday.
(SAfrica-Peace Talks-Congo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin's scheduled visits to
Japan and Russia in early September have been postponed due to the
immensity of flood control and disaster relief efforts in China.
</P>
<P>
The timetable for the visits will be rescheduled through
diplomatic channels between China and related
countries. (China-Jiang-Visit-Postponed) 
</P>
