<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Tells Jordan: Air Raids Target Terrorists, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton has
explained to Crown Prince Hassan, the Regent that the U.S. air
raids in Afghanistan and Sudan just targeted the terrorists, not
the Arabs and Muslims living there.
</P>
<P>
In a letter addressed to Hassan late Thursday night and carried
by Jordan's official Petra news agency Friday, Clinton rejected as
baseless the saying that the raids were targeted against Arabs and
Muslims in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The air raids were carried out upon a number of sites in
Afghanistan and the Sudan alleged by Washington as terrorist bases
or facilities, causing dozens of casualties. The attacks triggered
a wave of protest in Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. move came as a retaliation for the bombings of
U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian Royal Court and the government have not responded
to the letter as well as the air raids yet.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said Jordan is the U.S. third para-allied country in
the Middle East after Israel and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. economic and military aid for Jordan reached 225
million U.S. dollars in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
