<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Roster Foreign Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will unveil a national
soccer coach on next Tuesday from a shortlist of five Dutch
candidates, officials announced on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The Nigeria Football Association (NFA) will hold a meeting on
Tuesday to scrutinise those listed and the same day appoint the
new manager," said NFA spokesman Austin Mgbolu.
</P>
<P>
The candidates have been named as Henk Ten Cate, Wim Jansen,
Thijs Libregts, Ad de Mos and Wim Rijsbergen.
</P>
<P>
The position has been vacant since the World Cup finals in
July when Serbian Bora Milutinovic was in charge. Nigeria were
ousted 4-1 by Denmark in the second round.
</P>
<P>
The new coach will work with Nigerian local coach Amodu Shaibu
in preparing the team for the qualifying games for the 2000
African Nations Cup in Zimbabwe. Nigeria play their first
qualifying match against Burkina Faso in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
