<HEADLINE> Symposium Held on Industrialization of Gene Engineering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on China's
industrialization of gene engineering opened today in Hangzhou,
capital of Zhejiang Province in east China.
</P>
<P>
The three-day symposium is being attended by gene engineering
experts, industrialists and financiers from China and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the symposium will discuss and exchange views
on the history and future of gene engineering industrialization in
the world, China's industrialization of gene engineering and
strategies to be taken, roles to be played by Chinese financial
sectors, and fund raising for gene engineering projects.
</P>
<P>
Mang Keqiang, chairman of the China Gene Engineering Society;
Li Zaiping, academician of the China Engineering Academy; and Chen
Runsheng, researcher with the Bio-Physics Research Institute under
the Chinese Academy of Sciences, today delivered speeches on
research into the order of human genes and discovery of
bio-pharmaceuticals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
