<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Airport Insured Against Property Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- PICC Property, China's largest
property insurer, wrote an 8-billion-yuan (966 million US dollars)
policy on the Pudong International Airport, covering all risks
that might occur during construction of the first phase of the
airport.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the Shanghai Pudong International Airport is
one of the largest infrastructures to be built during the
1996-2000 period in Shanghai. The project involves 13.56 billion
yuan (1.6 billion US dollars) in total investment, with an annual
handling capacity of 20 million passengers and 750,000 tons of
cargo.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the first phase of the airport was launched in
October of 1997, and is scheduled to be completed and become
operational before Oct. 1, next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
