<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> T.N. Environment Program Chief to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Klaus Topfer, Executive
Director of the United Nations Environment Program (UNEP), is due
Nairobi-based UNEP announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
Topfer is duled to visit China's capital Beijing and the
biggest city of Shanghai and hold talks with Xie Zhenhua,
Minister of State Environmental Protection Administration of
China and some other Chinese high-level leaders, the UNEP aid in
a statement.
</P>
<P>
He will also act as "co-host" with Xie at a ceremony to launch
an electronic version of the report titled with "State of the
Environment in China" in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He will then visit Shanghai, meet with leaders of Shanghai
Municipality over urban environmental issues and attend the
International Workshop on Sustainable Development in Asia there.
</P>
<P>
The UNEP said that the flooding China is fighting against will
be high on the agunda during Topfer's visit.
</P>
<P>
The flooding follows exceptionally heavy seasonal rainfall
which might be linked to other unusual climatic events occurring
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
After Topfer's visit, UNEP will be in a better position to
assess the situation and to advise on ways in which the U.N.
system might be able to contribute assistance if required, said
the U.N. environment body. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
