<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Sales/Production Ratio Rises in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- China's sales/production ratio
of industrial products reached 96.29 percent in July, up 1.39
percent over the January-June period, the State Statistics Bureau
announced today.
</P>
<P>
A bureau official attributed the growth to an upturn in
China's consumer market and the efforts made by firms to
restrict their production.
</P>
<P>
He also predicted that the country's industrial growth rate
will be higher in the second half of this year as the
government's policies to stimulate the economy gradually take
effect.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and
Sichuan Province are positioned at the two ends of the list in
this regard. Following a 100-percent sales/production ratio in
June, the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region registered the same high ratio in July. Others
topping the list include Hainan Province and Chongqing
Municipality.
</P>
<P>
In July, the country's industrial growth rate stood at 7.6
percent, 0.3 percentage points lower than in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
