<HEADLINE> Hainan Butterfly Symposium Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A four-day symposium on butterfly
research ended today in Sanya, Hainan Province of south China.
</P>
<P>
It attracted more than 80 scholars and researchers from 16
Chinese provinces including Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
During the symposium, the first of its kind held in
China, Experts exchanged views on research of the differences
between butterfly culture in China and abroad, classification of
China's butterflies, and the protection and exploitation of the
nation's butterfly resources.
</P>
<P>
China has abundant butterfly resources. Experts noted that 12
categories and 1,600 species of butterflies are found throughout
the world, with 11 categories and more than 1,300 species in
China.  
</P>
