<HEADLINE> Kagame in Zambia for Talks With Chiluba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Rwandan Vice President Paul
Kagame has paid a one-day visit to Zambia amid tight security as
Lusaka continues pursuing peace efforts to resolve the three-week
conflict in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
Kagame, who doubles as Defense Minister was met at the Lusaka
International Airport Thursday morning by Vice-President Christon
Tembo and was immediately driven to the State House, where he
held a closed-door meeting with President Frederick Chiluba,
Zambia Daily Mail said Friday.
</P>
