<HEADLINE> EU Grants Flood Relief Aid to Slovakia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said on
Friday that it had earmarked 500,000 ECU (550,000 U.S. dollars) in
humanitarian aid for victims of the floods in Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
The aid, to be managed by the European Community Humanitarian
Office, will enable Austrian and German non-governmental
organizations to carry out emergency relief programs.
</P>
<P>
The commission fund will cover such emergency relief items as
blankets, hygiene products and medical supplies.
</P>
<P>
Floods hit the eastern part of Slovakia in late July, claiming
35 lives, most of them children in villages and gypsy
encampments. Some 3,500 people had to be evacuated from the
hardest-hit areas, commission officials said. 
</P>
