<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Propose Formation of ASEAN Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will propose the
formation of an ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations)
parliament in the forthcoming ASEAN Inter-Parliamentary
Organization (AIPO) meeting, Indonesia's house speaker said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters after a meeting with President B.J.
Habibie, House of Representatives (DPR) Speaker Harmoko said the
president as well as the DPR leadership had all agreed that the
proposal will be tabled at the AIPO meeting.
</P>
<P>
The AIPO meeting will take place in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, on
August 24-28. Harmoko will lead the Indonesian delegation to
attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko said the ASEAN Parliament could be set up without ever
having to interfere in ASEAN member countries' internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, it could serve as a vehicle for the
formulation of common stances or policies in support of the ASEAN
region's development, he said.
</P>
<P>
If the proposal was approved and Indonesia was asked to provide
a venue for the body, "we will, of course, be ready to meet the
request," Harmoko said.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN comprises Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, Brunei,
Singapore, the Philippines, Laos, Vietnam and Myanmar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
