<HEADLINE> PICC Pays One Billion Yuan For Flood Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The People's Insurance Company
of China (PICC) today announced that it has so far paid one
billion yuan (120 million US dollars) in indemnities against
economic losses in flooded areas.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the PICC has sent 10 working teams to
flood-stricken areas in Fujian, Hunan, Hubei and Jiangxi provinces
to evaluate losses and handle compensations. The PICC branches at
various levels have dispatched over 2,000 working groups to
distribute the compensation.
</P>
<P>
So far, the insured properties transferred or evacuated from
the floodwaters are valued at more than 6 billion yuan (725
million US dollars), and PICC compensation has helped more than
4,300 flooded enterprises to resume production.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the PICC's branch companies and its 130,000
employees have donated cash and materials valued at over 53
million yuan (6.4 million US dollars) to the flooded areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
