<HEADLINE> Pakistan Protests against Killing of Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Friday lodged a
strong protest against the U.S. overnight missile attacks on
alleged terrorist facilities in Afghanistan which resulted
casualties inside Pakistan border.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. forces on Thursday night attacked with cruise missiles
six sites in Afghanistan, located close to the Pakistani border,
which are believed to be the hideouts of the anti-American Saudi
millionaire Osama bin Ladin.
</P>
<P>
"On the presumption of violation of our sovereignty, we have
lodged a protest with the U.S. government," the spokesman said in
a special news briefing here Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Thursday's missile attacks have also resulted some
casualties about 10 to 15 km beyond the Pakistani border, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the U.S. Charge d'affaires was summoned
to the Foreign Office and a protest was lodged with him.
</P>
<P>
He said "the U.S. official expressed his regrets over the
incident and said it must be a result of a technical error."
</P>
<P>
He said that the U.S. attack has caused outrage and aggravated
the situation in the neighboring Afghanistan, which, following a
decade of superpower military intervention, continues to be in the
grip of turmoil and internal conflict. 
</P>
