<HEADLINE> Construction of Xiaolangdi Water Control Project Goes Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Xiaolangdi
water control project on the Yellow River, China's second longest,
has not been affected so far by rising waters during the flood
season, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
The multi-purpose project in central China's Henan Province, is
scheduled for completion in the year 2001. Construction of the
project is progressing smoothly, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The project consists of an earth-and-rock filled dam that will
be 1,667 meters long and 154 meters high with 16 tunnels to
release floodwaters.
</P>
<P>
Both digging of the tunnels and construction of the gigantic
hall housing generating units have already been completed, and
installation work for the generating units has been started.
</P>
</TEXT>
