<HEADLINE> Torrential Rains Could Cause New Flooding on Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Major floods may hit the Yangtze
River again this weekend as heavy rainfall has continued in some
areas on the upper reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains have, since Wednesday, deluged seven
prefectures and cities in the northwestern areas of the Sichuan
Basin, which is located on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Flooding has occurred on the Jinsha, Fujian, Minjiang, Tuojiang
and Jialing, five major rivers of the Yangtze River system in
southwest Sichuan Province, stranding more than 7,300 local
residents.
</P>
<P>
The floodwaters of the five rivers are expected to flow into
the Yangtze River in Chongqing at around 5 a.m. on Sunday, causing
the Yangtze River's water level to exceed the official warning
line by one meter and its water flow to reach 52,000 cubic meters
per second.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the water levels of the five rivers exceed official
warning lines.
</P>
<P>
Official forecasts call for thunder showers across a wider area
in Sichuan today, with the precipitation in some places expected
to exceed 100 millimeters.
</P>
<P>
All stranded residents reportedly have been evacuated.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
