<HEADLINE> Bus Fares Rise in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The two bus companies in Macao
raised bus fares in Macao on Friday, claiming that this will help
them reduce losses.
</P>
<P>
Macao consists of three parts: the Macao peninsula and the
Taipa and Coloane islands. Buses have been a major means of
traveling in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The bus fares in the Macao peninsula was raised from 2.3
patacas to 2.5 patacas, and those for buses shuttling between the
peninsula and the two islands were raised by 0.3 and 0.5 patacas
respectively.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the price of monthly tickets will be raised from
180 to 210 patacas beginning from September.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, the Macao government approved the price
rises. However, many local residents expressed their complaints.
</P>
<P>
Eight patacas equals to one U.S. dollar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
