there was no official position by the executive body of the
European Union (EU) on the attacks that reportedly claimed 25
lives in Afghanistan and 12 in Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The commission is currently in its summer recess.
</P>
<P>
The Council of Ministers, a principal decision-making body of
the 15-nation EU, expressed its intention on January 26 this year
that the fight against international terrorism must be effective
no matter where international terrorist acts take place.
</P>
<P>
