<HEADLINE> Singapore Parliament Speaker to Attend AIPO Meetings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Parliament Speaker
Tan Soo Khoon will lead a 15-member delegation to the 19th ASEAN
Inter-Parliamentary Organization meetings to be held in the
Malaysian capital of Kuala Lumpur from August 23 to 28, according
to a Parliament press release Friday.
</P>
<P>
It said the AIPO general assembly will be devoted to
discussions on issues ranging from the regional financial
situation and sub-regional cooperation to the Nuclear
Non-Proliferation Treaty, combat of transnational crime and the
aging population.
</P>
<P>
Committees on political, economic, social and organizational
matters will be formed to discuss the respective issues, it said,
adding there will also be a forum under the title "The state of
ASEAN Economies."
</P>
<P>
AIPO delegates will also have dialogue meetings with
parliamentarians from observer countries, viz. Australia,
Cambodia, Canada, China, Japan, South Korea, New Zealand, Papua
New Guinea, Russia and the European Parliament, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
