<HEADLINE> Wuhan Wins Battle against Yangtze River Flood Crest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The sixth flood crest on the
Yangtze River passed through Wuhan early this morning after
tormenting local people for 26 hours.
</P>
<P>
The long period of high water in this industrial city in
central China was caused by the confluence of water from the
Yangtze, Yuanshui and Lishui rivers and Dongting Lake, which
formed a gigantic body of water, said a local flood-control expert.
</P>
<P>
During the last two days, more than 280,000 civilians and
soldiers struggled against the flood on the Yangtze and Hanjiang
river embankments around the clock. They dealt with 1,757
dangerous sections of embankments in heavy rain and strong wind.
</P>
<P>
Qian Yunlu, secretary of the Wuhan City Committee of the
Communist Party of China, and city Mayor Wang Shouhai patroled the
river embankments and extended their regards to flood-fighters
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The city had prepared 350,000 cubic meters of sand and stones,
1.13 million cubic meters of earth and 7 million plastic bags for
use against the flood crest, Wang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
