<HEADLINE> Russian State Duma Advises Yeltsin to Step Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma, or lower
house of parliament, voted Friday in favor of recommending
President Boris Yeltsin to step down voluntarily before the
expiry of his term of office in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The motion, put forward by the Agrarian Party, was passed
245-32 with no abstentions at an extraordinary session on the
country's financial crisis. Altogether 277 deputies of the
450-member Duma attended the session.
</P>
<P>
The Duma accused Yeltsin of "not taking measures to protect
the constitutional rights of citizens or ensure effective
interaction of government structures for overcoming the
financial, social and economic crisis in the country."
</P>
<P>
It said such a situation posed "a serious threat to the
national security, territorial integrity and independence of the
Russian Federation." 
</P>
