<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Friday on continued selling
pressure.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index fell 7.69
percent or 26.98 points to 324.06, the all-share Emas Index lost
5.79 points to 84.20, the Industrial Index shed 36.21 points to
669.56 and the Second Board Index dropped 1.98 points to 84.20.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmed gainers 538 to 60 while 76 counters were
unchanged, 248 counters untraded and 35 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover declined to 142.720 million shares valued at
214.507 million ringgit (about 51.073 million U.S. dollars) from
391.669 million shares valued at 548.277 million ringgit (about
130.542 million U.S. dollars) traded on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The main board volume decreased to 135.775 million shares
valued at 208.192 million ringgit (about 49.569 million U.S.
dollars) from 370.411 million shares worth 525.726 million ringgit
(about 125.172 million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover dropped to 6.945 million shares worth
6.316 million ringgit (about 1.503 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 21.258 million shares valued at 22.551 million ringgit
(about 5.369 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deals were down to 1.427 million shares valued at
5.185 million ringgit (about 1.234 million U.S. dollars) from
3.092 million shares valued at 2.988 million ringgit (about 0.711
million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 5.046
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
11.666 million shares, construction 11.809 million shares,
trading/services 44.220 million shares, infrastructure 941,000
shares, finance 31.647 million shares, hotels 468,000 shares,
properties 13.407 million shares, plantation 4.921 million shares,
mining 193,000 shares, trusts 75,000 shares, closed/fund 15,000
shares and loans 11.367 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
