<HEADLINE> Dengue Fever Spreads in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 21 (xinhua) -- In Vietnam 84,500 people have been
infected by dengue fever and 186 died by August 15, Vietnam news
agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The number increased three and four fold over the same period
last year, the preventive medicine department said.
</P>
<P>
The disease is spreading mainly in Vietnam's central and Mekong
Delta provinces. The worst is the Mekong Delta province of Ben Tre
with 13,332 patients including 25 deaths. There are 8,844 patients
in the central province of Quang Tri.
</P>
<P>
The number of patients is unlikely to decline in the provinces
of Kien Giang, An Giang, Dac Lac, Quang Binh and Kon Tum.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Health Minister Do Nguyen Phuong demanded the Hanoi
Institute of Traditional Medicine and the army to
study and produce easy-to-use traditional medicine packages to
help the prevention and control of the disease.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested the government to set up a dengue fever control
program, which requires 5.5 billion Vietnamese Dong (about 400
thousand U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
