<HEADLINE> Fire Kills Five at German Poorhouse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and 15
others injured in a fire on Friday at a poorhouse in the German
town of Altshausen in southwestern state of Baden-Wuerttemberg.
</P>
<P>
Ten of the injured were in serious condition, according to
press here.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation ruled out arson from outside as the cause
of the fire that broke out at 1.20 a.m. (local time) at the
state-run hostel. The two-storied building accommodated 40
residents, most of whom were elderly people.
</P>
<P>
It took three hours to extinguish the fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
