<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former S. African President Found Guilty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Former South African state
president P. W. Botha was Friday found guilty for his refusal to
appear at a Truth and Reconciliation Commission (TRC) hearing.
</P>
<P>
The 82-year-old Botha now faces a jail sentence of up to two
years and/or a fine of up to 20,000 Rand (3,200 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Botha was found to have contravened the Promotion of National
Unity and Reconciliation Act by ignoring a TRC subpoena to attend
a hearing on the now-defunct state security council, which he
chaired in the 1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
