<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Study: Oil Related Workers at Higher Risk of Kidney Cancer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A study released Thursday
said that oil related job may raise risk for kidney cancer.
</P>
<P>
The study, published in the latest issue of the Journal of
Occupational and Environmental Medicine, has been conducted by
Dr. Eero Pukkala of the Finnish Cancer Registry in Helsinki.
</P>
<P>
Pukkala, who tracked the cancer histories of nearly 9,500
Finnish oil refinery workers for an average of 18 years,
discovered "significantly elevated" rates of kidney cancer among
workers -- rates two to three times higher than those found among
the general population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
