<HEADLINE> 2 Israeli Soldiers Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli soldiers were killed
overnight in south Lebanon by a Lebanese guerrillas roadside bomb,
the National Broadcast Network radio reported Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
The remote-controlled bomb set off when the two Israelis in
their car passed at Golea Shqif village in the edge of the Israeli
occupied south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The deadly blast brought to 12 the number of the Israelis
killed in south Lebanon since the start of this year while 76
others were wounded during the same period.
</P>
<P>
Another radio report said the attack was carried out by the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God.
</P>
<P>
The new fatalities came one day after Israeli Public Security
Minister Avigdor Kahalani threatened to strike Lebanon's
infrastructure facilities each time an Israeli soldier was killed
in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
He said that could force the Lebanese government to deploy army
on the borders to maintain security and prevent guerrillas from
using the south as a base to attack Israel.
</P>
<P>
He issued the warnings after one Israeli soldier was killed
and four others wounded also at Soujod by the roadside bomb on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a 1,200-square-kilometer self-declared
security zone in south Lebanon in 1985 to protect its north from
cross-border attack by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by the
Hezbollah has been fighting against Israeli occupation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
