<HEADLINE> Hundreds of Houses Razed in Jakarta Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of houses were burned
down in a fire which broke out in densely-populated Kenari village
in Senen, Central Jakarta, Friday.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which began at 9:15 a.m. and was put out by the
Central Jakarta Fire Department at 11 a.m., was allegedly caused
by a stove that exploded, according to eyewitnesses.
</P>
<P>
"No one was hurt or killed during the fire. We are still
gathering details about material losses," Kenari village head
Sukarna told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Fire victims will temporarily be sheltered in a nearby building
owned by the Betawi Consultative Board and in the village
administration building.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another fire broke out at 6 a.m. at a timber company
in East Jakarta, burning hundreds of cubic meters of timber.
</P>
<P>
An official of East Jakarta Fire Department, Narso, told
reporters that nine fire engines were sent to put out the fire and
that the cause of the fire is still being investigated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
