<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flood Victims Well Cared For (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Living in temporary huts and tents, the displaced villagers of
Changfu Village in Yueyang City around Dongting Lake look content.
</P>
<P>
As usual, rice, vegetables and meat compose their daily meals,
and access to clean running water is no problem. For those who
become ill, doctors are available for timely treatment. Improvised
toilets are also being provided.
</P>
<P>
Figures show that Yueyang City has built over 30,000 huts and
tents and used about 100 schools to accommodate over 200,000 flood
victims.
</P>
<P>
Over 700 tons of rice, 20 tons of instant noodles, over 10 tons
of biscuits, 6.5 tons of canned porridge, huge amounts of mineral
water, and five million yuan (602,400 U.S. dollars) worth of
medicines have been distributed by the city.
</P>
<P>
Hunan Province has so far allocated 55 million yuan (6.62
million U.S. dollars) in relief funds, 12,000 tons of grain, and
over 1.1 million pieces of clothing to the flood victims.
</P>
<P>
 Anhui Province: 370,000 People Move to Safe Places
</P>
<P>
According to today's People's Daily, Anhui Province has
evacuated over 370,000 flood-affected people to safe places. They
have settled in over 18,000 improvised huts, 13,000 vacated rooms,
or in the homes of friends and relatives.
</P>
<P>
Over 24 million yuan (2.89 U.S. dollars) in relief funds and
over 100 tons of instant noodles, biscuits, bread and bottled
water also have been sent to the victims.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
