<HEADLINE> Third Songhua River Flood Crest Passing Harbin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This level, accompanied by a flow rate of 17,400 cubic meters
per second, is 2.72 meters higher than the danger mark, and 0.77
meters higher than the 1957 record, according to latest reports.
</P>
<P>
The peak will take some time to recede as the upriver water
level remains high, and it will likely fluctuate, experts said,
adding that the water level grew by 0.02 meters over the past 10
hours.
</P>
