<HEADLINE> Construction Begins on Northwest Thermal Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Work on the construction of the
largest thermal power plant in northwestern Gansu Province began
this week.
</P>
<P>
The Pingliang Thermal Power Plant will use the rich coal
resources of the province to ease power shortage at the start of
the next century.
</P>
<P>
The Huating coal mine, the province's largest, has a verified
coal reserve of around 3.3 billion tons.
</P>
<P>
The plant will have four generators with a combined generating
capacity of 1.2 million kilowatts with the first going into
operation in the year 2000, and by the year 2003, all the four
generating units will be running.
</P>
<P>
The Pingliang plant will cost a total of 5.8 billion yuan
including 2 billion yuan loans from Japan. 
</P>
