this country and yet, for years, poverty has endured," he said,
stressing that all sectors of the society should join hands in
providing for the basic needs of the people.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that we can overcome this because of our
resolve and determination, because of our supporters like you,"
Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
He committed himself to re-channeling the funds for the pork
barrel of the congress to social service projects, saying he will
try to make sure that congressmen remain legislators and not
contractors.
</P>
<P>
Vice President and Social Welfare and Development Secretary
Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo said that nearly 142 million pesos (3.3
million U.S. dollars) has already been pledged by a number of
NGOs, international funding agencies, business establishments in
the Philippines and other organizations to help the government
expand social services. 
