<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passenger Plane Forced-Lands at Bangladeshi Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A Qatar Airlines plane with 232
passengers and crew on board made an emergency landing at the Zia
International Airport here Thursday, causing the suspension of all
flight operations for 11 hours, press reports here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
All the passengers and crew members came out of the damaged
aircraft safely through the emergency chutes and all domestic and
international flights were delayed while incoming flights were
diverted to other destinations.
</P>
<P>
The Doha, Qatar-bound Airbus-300, flight No. QTR-345, with 222
passengers including eight children and 10 crew members narrowly
escaped a major accident as its rear wheels caught fire before
takeoff at 7 a.m. local time. Three passengers were hurt during
the emergency exit from the aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one international flights of different airlines and 10
domestic flights of the Bangladesh Biman were postponed due to the
accident. The airport resumed normal flight operation at about
6:30 p.m. after the plane was removed from the runway.
</P>
<P>
The Civil Aviation Authority has formed a five-member committee
headed by B.K. Biswas, deputy director of the Aircraft Engineering
Department of the Bangladesh Biman, to investigate the accident.
</P>
<P>
The mishap took place after the plane suffered a bird-strike to
its engine when it was preparing for the takeoff.
</P>
<P>
The pilot implemented the engine shut-down procedures and
applied emergency brakes which resulted in overheating in its
undercarriage, according to the reports. Eight wheels at the rear
were badly damaged, and the landing gears and some other parts of
the aircraft were also damaged by the fire, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Qatar Airlines was making arrangements to fly the passengers,
mostly Bangladeshis, to Doha and the Airbus would be repaired in a
few days, the reports added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980821.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
