<HEADLINE> Australian Soccer Chief Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Soccer Australia
David Hill resigned suddenly late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hill also stepped down as chairman of Sydney Water to
concentrate on the imminent Australian federal election, where he
will stand as the Labor Party candidate.
</P>
<P>
The Soccer Australia board is expected to meet on August 29 to
choose a new chairman. 
</P>
