<HEADLINE> Jose Carreras China Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- One of the world's best known
tenors, Jose Carreras, will give a solo concert in China at
Beijing's Great Hall of the People on October 14.
</P>
<P>
He will be accompanied by the National Opera Orchestra
conducted by Enrique Ricci, according to organizers.
</P>
<P>
Carreras will follow Luciano Pavarotti and Placido Domingo in
holding a solo concert at the Great Hall.
</P>
<P>
Carreras, born in 1946 in Barcelona, has what has been
described as a "fascinating sweet voice", and audience throughout
the world have admired his extraordinary mastery of music.
</P>
<P>
His favorite opera roles are Rudolph from Puccini's La Boheme
and Don Jose from Bizet's Carmen.  
</P>
