<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Hold Civil Service Examination: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- About 82,000 candidates will
compete for 1,264 posts in the 20th Bangladesh Civil Service (BCS)
examination which is expected to be held later this year, a press
report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Only one in every 65 of the candidates who have submitted
application forms can eventually succeed in the competition.
</P>
<P>
The number of applications submitted this year was 2,000 more
than those of the 18th BCS exams held last year, when 80,213
candidates were vying for 1,979 posts, The Independent newspaper
quoted Kabirul Alam Khan, controller of the Bangladesh Public
Service Commission (PSC) administering the exams, as saying
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the 17th exams, 65,502 candidates applied for 2,026 posts,
and the 19th exams were a special one for the Fisheries Cadre, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Over 200,000 application forms had been sold through Sonali
Bank branches across the country and in London and at the PSC
central secretariat, and more application forms were expected to
he submitted soon, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
