<HEADLINE> Serna Eliminates Graf in Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- German star Steffi Graf
surffered another defeat after her comeback Thursday when she was
beaten by Spain's Magui Serna 4-6, 4-6 in the third round of the
Canadian Open in Montreal.
</P>
<P>
The loss ruined an anticipated Graf-Jana Novotna
quarter-final. The Czech second seed advanced by trouncing
Italy's Silvia Farina 6-1, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Top seeded Martina Hingis of Switzerland reached the
quarter-finals after a 6-3, 6-0 win over Japan's Ai Sugiyama.
Hingis won an exciting, side-to-side 29-stroke rally.
</P>
<P>
Monica Seles, the three-time defending champion at the
Canadian Open, defeated Indonesian Yayuk Basuki 6-3, 6-3 and will
meet German Anke Huber in Friday's quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The 21st-ranked Huber, playing in her second tournament since
foot surgery in April, edged eighth-seeded Amanda Coetzer of
South Africa 7-5, 7-6 (8-6).
</P>
<P>
"I just made so many mistakes on my backhand," Graf was quoted
as saying. "and I really didn't feel like I was getting into the
match.
</P>
<P>
"I do have to say that she served really well and made very
few mistakes."
</P>
<P>
Graf was obviously shaken by her erratic and uninspired play.
</P>
<P>
She has won only four matches at three tournaments over the
past four weeks. That concern was likely the reason she has
accepted a wild card into the WTA Tour tournament in New Haven,
Connecticut, starting next Monday. reports said.
</P>
<P>
Seles was able to outhit Basuki from the baseline and now she
will meet Huber, whom she beat in the Canadian Open final in
Toronto a year ago. She holds an 8-0 career head-to-head
advantage on Huber and has never lost a set.
</P>
<P>
Hingis next meets the winner of ninth-seeded Irina Spirlea of
Romania and 14th-seeded Sandrine Testud of France. That match was
postponed by rain at 6-6 in the first set.
</P>
<P>
Also postponed was third-seeded Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario of
Spain and France's Nathalie Tauziat, seeded 11. Tauziat led 4-3.
</P>
</TEXT>
