<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Provinces Along Yellow River Preparing For Possible Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- While nearly 10 million people
are fighting the flooding on the Yangtze, Nenjiang, and Songhua
rivers, provinces along the Yellow River have also been busy
repairing flood control facilities to prepare for possible
flooding.
</P>
<P>
The Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region has had more rainfall this
year than usual and the regional flood control and drought relief
headquarters has told various areas to prepare a flood and rescue
and evacuation plan. The region has spent 22 million yuan
repairing dilapidated facilities and this year.
</P>
<P>
Authorities in Shaanxi Province, 67 percent of which is in the
Yellow River valley, have told local officials to make the flood
fight on the Yellow River a priority and to prepare for possible
flooding on the Yellow and Weihe rivers, and have spent 96 million
yuan repairing flood control facilities, and organized 3,900 flood
rescue teams.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi Province has been keeping a close watch on rainfall and
the water level in the Yellow River and has made an effort to
clear obstacles in the river and has prepared materials for
combating floods. Flood control and drought relief organizations
have a 24-hour work system for monitoring the situation on the
Yellow River. Local meteorology and hydrology offices have
intensified weather and water level watches and monitoring of
mountain floods.
</P>
<P>
Henan Province has been carefully inspecting its flood control
facilities and has prepared a great number of materials for flood
fighting. It has also improved hydrological data gathering
equipment on the Yellow River and its telecommunications equipment
in different counties to help the flow of information and has
organized a team of one million people to fight the floods.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
