<HEADLINE> Jewish Settler Stabbed to Death in Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A Jewish settler was stabbed
to death in a Jewish settlement in Hebron late Thursday night,
the second killing of the type in West Bank in less than a month.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio reported Friday that 63-year-old rabbi Shlomo
Raanan was knifed by a terrorist who broke into his home. The
attacker then set fire to the house before he fled, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli soldiers combed the settlement and declared a closed
military zone following the incident. Palestinian security forces
had been notified and were searching their side of the city.
</P>
<P>
This was the second fatal attack against Jewish settlers in
less than a month. Two Jewish settlers were ambushed and killed on
the evening of August 4 in a settlement near another West Bank
town of Nablus.
</P>
<P>
Following the attack in Hebron, home to about 500 Jewish
settlers surrounded by more than 100,000 Palestinians, some Jewish
settler leaders and right-wingers in Israel's parliament urged the
government to halt its talks with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The talks, started a month ago, have not achieved any
progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
