<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- At least five Pakistanis were killed and more than
10 others seriously injured Thursday night in U.S. missile strikes
on the afghan city of Khost bordering Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
An Islamabad-based spokesman for Harakat Ul Mujahideen, which
runs a military base in Khost for Kashmiris, told Xinhua that the
injured have been taken to a hospital in Pakistan's border town of
Miran Shah. The United States launched missile attacks against
what it said was a complex of terrorists allegedly run by Saudi
exile Osama bin Laden about 150 kilometers south of the Afghan
capital of Kabul close to the Pakistani border.
(US-Afghanistan-Strikes)
