<HEADLINE> Anti-doping Agency Proposed by IOC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic
Committee (IOC) is to set up an independent anti-doping agency in
a bid to step up wars against banned drugs.
</P>
<P>
An Olympic Movement Anti-Doping Agency will be proposed by IOC
in its anti-drugs conference next February, IOC president Juan
Antonio Samaranch announced here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new agency will be responsible for carrying out
out-of-competition testing in IOC member countries and nations
and coordinating 26 IOC-accredited drug-testing centers.
</P>
<P>
The new organization, with headquarters in Lausanne, will be
independent of IOC and be funded by the billions of dollars that
IOC received from TV rights for the Games. 
</P>
