<HEADLINE> Looking After China's Flood Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Civil
Affairs has told people to give money and goods to local civil
affairs or other departments that are approved for receiving
donations.
</P>
<P>
In a circular made public Thursday, the ministry said that
money and clothes can also be given directly to civil affairs
departments in flooded areas, or donations made to the Ministry of
Civil Affairs and China Charity Federation.
</P>
<P>
Post offices will send such donations free of charge, along
with a letter of thanks.
</P>
<P>
Foreign governments and individual donors can send their money
and goods to the Red Cross Society of China, the Civil Affairs
Ministry of China or to Chinese embassies and consulates in their
own countries,
 The circular asked people not to take part in other donation
activities held under the pretence of providing flood relief, and
not to be fooled by these.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, China Youth Daily reports that some
people have used donation hotlines to disrupt the normal process
of donations and some people have put donation boxes on the
streets to cheat donors out of their money.  
</P>
</TEXT>
