<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grenade Attack Kills One in Phnom Penh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A 45-year old driver for
Kyodo News Serves was killed in a grenade attack Thursday night
outside the Cambodian Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The incident shattered the relatively peaceful post-election
calm and raised the concerns about the future of the new coalition
government.
</P>
<P>
The attack followed a series of confrontations between police
and Sam Rainsy party supporters, who were attempting to sleep at
the Interior Ministry compound with election ballots, witnesses
said.
</P>
<P>
Sieng Sean, who had worked for Kyodo since the Untac era, was
struck by grenade shrapnel in the back of the head at about 2300
local time on Norodom Boulevard as he waited for his colleague to
return from interviewing Sam Rainsy, said police and witnesses.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the attack, Sam Rainsy was detained inside
the compound for three hours, where he was preparing to sleep with
party members who were guarding ballots from the July 26 polls.
</P>
<P>
Several minutes after the explosion, witnesses said Interior
Ministry guards pointed their guns at Sam Rainsy -- who raised his
hands -- and fired one round near his feet.
</P>
<P>
"They threatened to kill us many times, I thought I was going
to be another Ho Sok tonight," Sam Rainsy said at about two
o'clock Friday as he was leaving the compound with UN escort. Ho
Sok was the Funcinpec general slain at the compound last year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts suspected it was a deliberate political terrorism.
Government spokesman Khieu Kanharith said: "We suspect this might
be an attempt to stir trouble. But we assume nothing."
</P>
<P>
He said a complain would be filed with the municipal court
Friday because Sam Rainsy entered the ministry compound.
</P>
<P>
Sieng Sean was survived by his wife, a daughter and two sons.
</P>
<P>
"My father never had a quarrel with anyone. It was perhaps related
to politics. I was very shocked. I just had dinner with him this
evening," his son said sadly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
