<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Reassert Control Over State Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian government will
reassert its control over businesses in which it has a
stakeholding in order to reclaim lost profits, it was announced
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Minister of Economy Leonid Mininh said the government
would increase its representation in its business interests so it
would have more influence in management.
</P>
<P>
The state holds shares in 6,500 companies which made a net
profit of three billion hryvnya (1.67 billion U.S. dollars) last
year, but only 20 million hryvnya (11.1 million dollars) was
turned over to the treasury, said Mininh.
</P>
<P>
Of the 6,500 businesses, the government held a controlling
interest in only 2,300 and posted representatives in just 1,318.
</P>
<P>
The government intended to increase the number of
representatives under a presidential mandate signed on July 4
concerning the management of state assets, added the
minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
