<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Delegation Ends Visit to Slovakia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRATISLAVA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Chinese
National People's Congress left here for home Thursday, winding up
a four-day official visit to Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, parliament leaders of the two countries
exchanged views on further developing Sino-Slovak relations,
especially ties between the Chinese NPC and the Slovak National
Council.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation was led by Peng Peiyun, vice chairwoman
of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Both sides believed that the visit would help deepen mutual
understanding and promote cooperation between the two countries in
the fields of politics, trade, science and technology and culture.
</P>
<P>
Slovak Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar also met with Peng Peiyun
during the delegation's stay in the country.
</P>
<P>
Peng invited Slovak National Council Chairman Ivan Gashparovic
to visit China and the invitation was accepted.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived in Bratislava on Monday, following their
trips to Bulgaria, Yugoslavia and Croatia. 
</P>
