<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Donations For Flood Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A telephone survey in Beijing
found that more than 88 percent of the city's citizens have
donated money or goods for flood-hit parts of China and 100
percent of its people say they want to make a donation.
</P>
<P>
The survey of 324 families was done by the China Youth Daily,
one of China's most popular newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The paper said, however, that over half of the donors worry that
the donations may not reach flood victims and that a donation
distribution monitoring system is urgently needed.
</P>
<P>
A previous survey on August 8 showed only 21 percent of the
people responding to the call for donations.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that 76 percent of the units and 67
percent of the neighborhood committees in the Chinese capital have
arranged donation activities.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
