<HEADLINE> Shanghai Publicizes Regulations to Protect Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Regulations to protect the
elderly have been approved by the Municipal People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, effective on Jan. 1, 1999, are designed to
ensure that the elderly enjoy personal safety, marriage freedom,
guarantee of property, the right to be supported by their
children, and the right to use and rent their houses.
</P>
<P>
With 17.4 per cent of its population -- 2.3 million people --
above 60, Shanghai is the first municipality in the country to
become an aging city.
</P>
