<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Province Establishes Center for Endangered Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province
has set up a center for the protection of endangered plants in
Ningshan County.
</P>
<P>
The 2,000-hectare center, the largest of its kind in northwest
China, has more than 450 kinds of woody plants including some
endangered species such as Douglas fir, spear-wood trees,
epaulette-trees, and emmenopterys henryis.
</P>
<P>
The center also has more than 1,000 kinds of herbs, plants for
medicinal use and microorganisms.
</P>
<P>
Ningshan County is situated on the southern slope of the
Qinling Mountain, which is considered the geographical border
between the south and the north in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
