<HEADLINE> Quartey Stripped of WBA Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Welterweight champion Ike
Quartey of Ghana was Thursday stripped of his title by the World
Boxing Association (WBA).
</P>
<P>
WBA president Elias Cordoba said Quartey had failed to defend
his title within a reasonable timeframe.
</P>
<P>
Quartey had twice pulled out of defences against No.1
contender Andrei Pestraiev of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The WBA said Pestriaev will fight Mexican Jose Luis Lopez, a
former World Boxing Organization champion, for the vacant
welterweight title. 
</P>
