<HEADLINE> Huge Investment for Fujian Tourist Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Three billion U.S. dollars of
overseas investment has gone into tourist projects in east China's
Fujian Province over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
These projects include a film city, entertainment centers, and
resorts at coastal and nature reserve areas.
</P>
<P>
Local people are also involved in the development of tourist
programs. In Pinghe county, 70 million yuan has been accumulated
to set up tourist facilities near the Sanping Temple, while in
Hui'an county, more than 10 million yuan and donations of
stone-carving sculptures were collected to build a stone-works
museum.
</P>
<P>
Fujian, which received over 10 million overseas tourists duing
the first six months this year, ranks fourth in the country in
overseas-related tourist income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
