<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Officers Spreading Coup Rumors: Defense Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Powerful military officers,
including some retired generals, are spreading coup rumors to stop
the Joseph Estrada administration from investigating fund
irregularities at a military financial institution, Manila
Bulletin reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Defense Secretary Orlando Mercado as saying
that no psychological operation can prevent the probers from
conducting an investigation on the anomalies.
</P>
<P>
Mercado said he has received information on who are responsible
for the spreading of the coup rumors but declined to identify
them.
</P>
<P>
"This is what we call psychological operations and the
objective, I believe, is to try to rattle us or try to see how
much resolve we have thinking that we would run away with our tail
between our two legs," the defense chief said.
</P>
<P>
Mercado said he confided the coup rumor issue to President
Estrada last Wednesday and the president instructed him to
continue with the investigation, "whether there is a coup or
none."
</P>
<P>
He said he has also been getting death threats but added these
will not deter him from digging deeper into the anomalies and
nailing down the culprits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
