<HEADLINE> Four Plane hijackers Sentenced to Death in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 20 (Xinhua) -- An anti-terrorist special
court in Pakistan Thursday sentenced four people to death for
hijacking a Fokker plane of the Pakistan International Airlines
(PIA) on May 24.
</P>
<P>
The sentence was handed down by Justice Saleem Ahmad at the
court in Hyderabad and Mirpurkhas divisions, reports reaching here
said.
</P>
<P>
The four Baloch nationalists hijacked the PIA aircraft on an
inland flight from Turbat, a town in the southern Balochistan
province, to Karachi, five days before Pakistan conducted its
nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
They were opposed to nuclear testing in Balochistan and
protesting against the federal government's "discriminatory
attitude" towards the country's largest province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
