<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Warns Against Contraband Cigarettes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The National Tobacco
Enterprise of Ethiopia warned Thursday that all cigarettes
intercepted while being smuggled into the country have been found
expired and hazardous for health.
</P>
<P>
Ayalew Abebe, representative of the trade department of the
national tobacco monopoly, told the Ethiopian News Agency that
the enterprise has recently burned 65,000 cartons of contraband
cigarettes after examinations proved that all were expired and
dangerous.
</P>
<P>
Ayalew explained that the cigarettes being smuggled into the
country are exposed to damages due to poor handling.
</P>
<P>
Any tobacco and tobacco products could be imported and
distributed only after they are certified by the National Tobacco
Enterprise, he said.
</P>
<P>
Examined imported cigarettes and tobacco products are marked
with the seal of the enterprise, he said, adding that those
tobacco without seal of the enterprise are unchecked and may be
dangerous for health. 
