<HEADLINE> Clinton to Address on U.S. Air Strikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
will make a televised address from the White House shortly after
returning to Washington on Thursday, the White House said.
</P>
<P>
Clinton cut short his vacation on the Massachusetts island of
Martha's Vineyard on Thursday after announcing two air strikes
on "terrorist-related" bases in Afghanistan and Sudan believed
to have been behind the bombings of U.S. embassies in Kenya
and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Joe Lockhart said he expected Clinton
to return to Washington at around 4:15 p.m. EDT (2015 GMT) and
will address from the Oval Office. 
</P>
