<HEADLINE> Britain Voices Support to U.S. Air Strikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
Thursday expressed strong support for the U.S. military air
strikes against alleged international terrorists in Afghanistan
and Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Blair said in a statement issued early Thursday that the
British government had been informed of the American airstrikes,
which were staged in retaliation for the recent bomb attacks on
U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
"The atrocities this month in Nairobi, Dar es Salaam and Omagh
(Northern Ireland) have shown the pain and suffering that
terrorism can bring to innocent people," Blair said.
</P>
<P>
Blair noted that Britain "strongly supports this American
action against international terrorists. Terrorists the world over
know that democratic governments will act decisively to prevent
their evil crimes."
</P>
<P>
A Downing Street spokeswoman said that Blair, who is on holiday
in France, would discuss the latest development with U.S.
President Bill Clinton by telephone Thursday evening.  
</P>
</TEXT>
