<HEADLINE> Sudanese President Condemns U.S. Air Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President Omar Hassan
al-Bashir issued a statement here Thursday night condemning the
U.S. attack on Sudan's facilities.
</P>
<P>
"This is a provocation to the Sudanese people," the president
said.
</P>
<P>
The Al-Shifa Pharmaceutical Factory on the outshirts of the
capital was air raided hours ago, allegedly in retaliation for the
terrorist bombing of U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania on August
7.
</P>
<P>
The three-story building of the factory was destroyed and
witnesses said the people on the night shift did not escape and
were feared killed.
</P>
<P>
They said four huge explosions were heard and the conflagration
caused by the attack is still burning.
</P>
<P>
There was no official figure of casualties. 
</P>
