<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Ghanaian Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister General
Chi Haotian met today with Major General Joseph Smith,
commander-in-chief of the Ghanaian Army.
</P>
<P>
Chi said the two countries have had friendly cooperative
relations since the 1960s in spite of the wide geographic
separation.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Ghanaian friendship is well founded, said Chi, adding
that both countries fought long and hard to win independence.
</P>
<P>
Chi expressed great appreciation of Ghana's support of the
one-China policy and stand on Tibet and human right issues.
</P>
<P>
He briefed the visiting guests on China's flood control
situation, and expressed gratitude to Ghana's concern and support
for the ongoing flood relief effort.
</P>
<P>
Smith said that Sino-Ghanaian relations are based on mutual
sincerity, and noted that Ghana has always attached great
importance to enhancing friendship and cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that Ghanaian President Jerry Rawlings considers China
a genuine friend and believes that all African countries should
establish friendly ties with it.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Qian Shugen, deputy chief of General Staff
of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, was present during the
meeting. 
</P>
