<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African House Passes Controversial Labor Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's National
Assembly Friday passed a highly controversial labor bill, which
aims to promote equal work place opportunities for previously
disadvantaged people.
</P>
<P>
The Employment Equity Bill cleared the lower house of
parliament by a vote of 214 to 72, South African Press
Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The bill was strongly rejected by historically white-dominated
parties, the National Party, the Democratic Party, Freedom Front
and African Christian Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
But traditionally black-based parties, the ruling African
National Congress (ANC), Inkatha Freedom Party and Pan Africa~?
Congress, voted in favor of the legislation.
</P>
<P>
The bill provides for businesses of more than 50 employees to
draw up plans to make the breakdown of their employees represent
the racial composition of the population.
</P>
</TEXT>
