<HEADLINE> 8 People Killed in Landslides in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Eight people died Friday
morning in Palpa district, western Nepal when their houses
collapsed in landslides caused by heavy rain, the official RSS
news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Six members of one family died in Khasyauli village and two
others died in neighboring Masyam village, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 people have died in floods and landslides across
the country during the monsoon season starting in June. 
</P>
