<HEADLINE> China Publishes Book by Croatian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- China's Central Compilation and
Translation Press recently published Croatian President Franjo
Tudjman's book entitled "The Wasteland of Historic Reality".
</P>
<P>
The book delves into the history of war and violence in the
former Yugoslavia. It provides Chinese readers with
greater insight into changes, major events and dignitaries in
modern Yugoslavia, as well as the national issue in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman, a legendary figure, served as a Yugoslavian general
during the World War II and later earned a Ph. D.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman has authored some 150 books, theses and essays on
history, military theory, philosophy and international
relations.
</P>
<P>
He was elected as the first president of the Republic of
Croatia in 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980821.0395 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets With Ghana Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
today spoke highly of Sino-Ghanaian friendly relations and voiced
his appreciation of the Ghana government's adherence to the "one
China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks during a meeting here today with a
delegation of Ghanaian women led by Nana Konadu Agyeman-Rawlings,
the first lady and president of the 31st of December Women's
movement of Ghana.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China (CPC) and the Chinese government
would continue to reinforce and advance Sino-Ghanaian cooperative
ties, which enjoys broad prospects, said Hu, also a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the current flood-control campaign in China, Hu
said that heavy floods rarely seen in history have taken place on
China's Yangtze, Nenjiang and Songhua rivers this year. However,
millions of the Chinese soldiers and citizens, under the staunch
leadership of the CPC and the Chinese government, have so far
overcome one flood crest after another, Hu noted.
</P>
<P>
The present flood-control situation remains very serious, Hu
said. "But we are resolved to fight through the flood and win the
final victory," he told Agyeman-Rawlings.
</P>
<P>
Hu also expressed his thanks for donations from
Agyeman-Rawlings to China's flood-hit areas.
</P>
<P>
Agyeman-Rawlings told Hu that the Ghanaian people have profound
feelings toward their Chinese counterparts and the exchanges
between the women of the two countries have promoted bilateral
friendship.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Ghanaian first lady said that she has witnessed
during this visit the great changes that have taken place in China
and the enormous progress the Chinese women have scored. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
