<DOCNO> XIE19980821.0396 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban to Give Befitting Reply if Attacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban authorities
have said that if they were attacked by Iran over the question of
its missing citizens, they will give a befitting reply to it.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here Friday evening the remarks
by the Taliban militia came in response to the warning of Iranian
Foreign Ministry spokesman, Mahmoud Mohammad that his country
would take all appropriate steps to release its kidnapped
diplomats.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the spokesman of the Iranian Foreign Ministry
said that Iran does not want to trespass the Afghan border.
However, he said that if the Taliban continued excesses on the
people in its border areas "then it will prove dangerous."
</P>
<P>
The Taliban militia said that they are ready for talks over the
question of the release of the Iranian truck drivers held by them
provided that Iran hands over General Malik, head of a major
faction in the Anti-Taliban Northern Alliance, to them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
